	<tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#666699" vAlign="TOP">
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">Sometimes, Sorry not interested, DOES NOT work.  I had a telemarketer call me in the middle of the afternoon.  I listened politely to his stuff and when he took a break, I politely said I'm not interested, please remove my phone number from your list.  Again, he tried to sell me something. Again, I repeated the above.  I repeated myself FOUR times before I got frustrated and hung up on him.  Time is money to them and they are taught to keep on hanging in there because the "sell" is there.  I refused to be hassled by someone that called me.  I like the idea of placing them on hold for as long as they will be on the line.  How long was that guy gonna try to sell me whatever?</font></p>
	
	<p><p><img src="/forums/images/sig_separator.gif" width="282" height="11" Alt="Hey! Watch where you point that thing!"><br>
